"{\"uid\": \"gizmodo.com-google-says-ai-olympics-ad-tested-well-before-inspiring-outrage-2000482900\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Reading time 2 minutes  Google's attempt to funnel Olympics excitement into its chatbot,Gemini, \\\"tested well before airing,\\\" the company said.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24, \"end\": 30, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 94, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9911334739197877, \"rank\": 0.008945844645041416, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon its debut, however, the ad repelled viewers by making artificial intelligence seem like a weak substitute for parenting and human creativity.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The negative response to \\\"Dear Sydney,\\\" which features a dad using Gemini to help his daughter write a fan letter, was so great that it drove Google to phase it out of TV rotation.\", \"from\": 291, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9911334739197877, \"rank\": 0.008945844645041416, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our goal was to create an authentic story celebrating Team USA,\\\" the tech giant said in a statement, adding, \\\"AI can be a great tool for enhancing human creativity, but can never replace it.\\\"\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999690772, \"rank\": 2.998991510795487e-11, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Google pulled the ad from its Olympics rotation.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It remains onYouTube, with the comments feature turned off.\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Google's ad centers on a dad (narrator) and his daughter.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's \\\"always been a runner\\\" and looks up to American hurdler and sprinter Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9902383406651152, \"rank\": 0.00985740847433703, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999996664087677, \"rank\": 2.527456448226146e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, she wants to \\\"show Sydney some love\\\" by sending some fan mail.\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 1009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999996664087677, \"rank\": 2.527456448226146e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dad explains, \\\"I am pretty good with words, but this has to be just right.\\\"\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\", \"score\": 0.999254003248537, \"rank\": 0.0007465536781518594, \"text\": \"Dad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Father\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, the paternal voice asks Gemini to help draft a fan letter to McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9911334739197877, \"rank\": 0.008945844645041416, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Who's That Girl\\\" by Eve cuts in (Eve's publisher, Universal Music Group, did not immediately respond a request for comment on the matter).\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1195, \"end\": 1198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\", \"score\": 0.6143491266387536, \"rank\": 0.6276275102382756, \"text\": \"Eve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\"}, {\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\", \"score\": 0.6143491266387536, \"rank\": 0.6276275102382756, \"text\": \"Eve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eve\"}, {\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Universal_Music_Group\", \"score\": 0.99996714488948, \"rank\": 3.285618390083831e-05, \"text\": \"Universal Music Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Universal_Music_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Universal_Music_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, asparkle graphictwirls and Google's chatbot generates a draft.\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad ends with the tagline, \\\"A little help from Gemini.\\\"\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9911334739197877, \"rank\": 0.008945844645041416, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite reportedlyperforming wellin tests by ad research firm System1, Google's commercial was not well received out in the real world.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero SUCKS,\\\"wroteNPR's pop-culture podcast host Linda Holmes on social media siteBlueSky.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.691282607967988e-12, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4239925187375893e-22, \"text\": \"Linda Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just so grossed out by the entire thing,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"AWashington Postcolumnist said it made herwant to\\\"throw a sledgehammer into the television.\\\"\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad also ad drew criticism from Reddit'sDaddit group, where some users described it as \\\"gross\\\" and \\\"inhuman.\\\"\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 2017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shelly Palmer, professor of advanced media at Syracuse University's communications school, argued in anessaythat the ad exaggerates Gemini's capabilities and sends the wrong message to parents.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2019, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999790843506, \"rank\": 1.0415469030265773e-08, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9911334739197877, \"rank\": 0.008945844645041416, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Google would have us believe that this young girl does not need to learn to articulate and describe her reality,\\\" Palmer wrote.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is criminally negligent.\\\"\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad also appeared on Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone'sInstagrama week ago.\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2399, \"end\": 2405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999996664087677, \"rank\": 2.527456448226146e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Do you really want to receive an ai generated letter?,\\\" one user asked.\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some commenters responded more positively.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This one made me teary,\\\" a user said.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[N]obody better to look up to,\\\" another replied.\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Google pulled the ad.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999999925416887, \"rank\": 7.443286720185982e-09, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another tech giant's ad also recently fell flat.\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Appleinspired some outragein May while attempting to extol tech's role in facilitating human creativity.\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The company's \\\"Crush\\\" ad starred an industrial crusher that slowly smashes a collection of creative objects - including numerous paint buckets, a piano, several books, and a sculpture.\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 3020, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the crusher lifts, it chillingly leaves an iPad behind in the objects' wake.\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3100, \"entities